	(26,18,'member_title','Coordinator of Outside Vendors, Sports Clinics and President of Sales; Kansas, Missouri, Nebraska, Wyoming, Iowa'),
	(27,18,'member_profile','I am entering my eighth year as a full-time fundraising consultant. I have been personally helped raise over $3 million for schools in the Midwest over those six years. I also have experience with a national fundraising company as a Region Director of Sales and have managed up to 30 fundraising franchises all over the Midwest and West Coast.\r\n\r\nI was a three-sport athlete at Omaha Bryan High School and played college baseball at Iowa State University. Some athletic achievements in high school are: Athlete of the Year at Omaha Bryan, All-State baseball, Metro District Champion in wrestling, and All-Division in football. At Iowa State I was team MVP and All Big XII. I received a Bachelors degree in Exercise Science at Iowa State and a Masters in Business Administration from Bellevue College.\r\n\r\nProfessionally, I\'ve coached at the high school and collegiate level and have also been the Director of Baseball with a youth baseball organization in Omaha. I\'ve had the opportunity to coach at the Junior College World Series and also the Nebraska State Tournament. Currently, I am coach at Shawnee Mission West High School in Overland Park, Kansas. \r\n\r\nOn a personal note, I am happily married to Keri Bahun and have twin daughters Faith and Rhyan.'),
