	(260,97,'testimonial_letter','As a cheerleading coach, I am often looking for a fundraiser that will be an effortless moneymaker. Because the girls foot the entire bill for their uniforms, it is also important to find a product that literally sells itself.\r\n\r\nWith Fundraising University and Kyle Johnson, I have found just that. Delightfully simple, our cookie dough fundraiser was a huge hit. Our nine girls easily outsold their previous goals, and some girls even earned enough money to pay entirely for their uniforms and camp!\r\n\r\nWith blitz night and the incentives afterwards, our girls and their parents have already asked for this same fundraiser next year. Pleasing our parents is always a huge accomplishment. Plus, I don’t really feel like I did any work at all. Kyle was always present, always communicative, and always knowledgeable.\r\n\r\nIt was painless. Kyle was accessible. The product is worthwhile. The girls were successful. For us, things just don’t get much better than that.'),
	(261,97,'testimonial_signature','Becky Thumann\r\nCheerleading Sponsor \r\nSchuyler Central High School'),
	(262,97,'sort_index',''),
	(263,97,'testimonialletter','<p>As a cheerleading coach, I am often looking for a fundraiser that will be an effortless moneymaker. Because the girls foot the entire bill for their uniforms, it is also important to find a product that literally sells itself.</p>\r\n<p>With Fundraising University and Kyle Johnson, I have found just that. Delightfully simple, our cookie dough fundraiser was a huge hit. Our nine girls easily outsold their previous goals, and some girls even earned enough money to pay entirely for their uniforms and camp!</p>\r\n<p>With blitz night and the incentives afterwards, our girls and their parents have already asked for this same fundraiser next year. Pleasing our parents is always a huge accomplishment. Plus, I don’t really feel like I did any work at all. Kyle was always present, always communicative, and always knowledgeable.</p>\r\n<p>It was painless. Kyle was accessible. The product is worthwhile. The girls were successful. For us, things just don’t get much better than that.</p>'),
	(264,18,'memberprofile','<p>I am entering my eighth year as a full-time fundraising consultant. I have been personally helped raise over $3 million for schools in the Midwest over those six years. I also have experience with a national fundraising company as a Region Director of Sales and have managed up to 30 fundraising franchises all over the Midwest and West Coast.</p>\r\n<p>I was a three-sport athlete at Omaha Bryan High School and played college baseball at Iowa State University. Some athletic achievements in high school are: Athlete of the Year at Omaha Bryan, All-State baseball, Metro District Champion in wrestling, and All-Division in football. At Iowa State I was team MVP and All Big XII. I received a Bachelors degree in Exercise Science at Iowa State and a Masters in Business Administration from Bellevue College.</p>\r\n<p>Professionally, I\'ve coached at the high school and collegiate level and have also been the Director of Baseball with a youth baseball organization in Omaha. I\'ve had the opportunity to coach at the Junior College World Series and also the Nebraska State Tournament. Currently, I am coach at Shawnee Mission West High School in Overland Park, Kansas.</p>\r\n<p>On a personal note, I am happily married to Keri Bahun and have twin daughters Faith and Rhyan.</p>'),
	(265,83,'memberprofile','<p>I have worked in the fundraising industry for 4 years now and serve as the Office Manager for Fundraising University. My core duties are accounting, artwork, setup of personalized discount products and design, coordination of Coaching Matters party - Annual Night at the Ballpark and The Nebraska Football Coaches Association Football parties. I also coordinate all Fundraising U clinics and communication from merchants and coaches.</p>'),
	(266,103,'_edit_last','1'),
	(267,103,'_edit_lock','1327015493:1'),
	(268,103,'member_name','Colin Shockey'),
	(269,103,'member_title','Nebraska and South Dakota'),
	(270,103,'member_phone','1-800-217-1962 ext 2'),
	(271,103,'member_email','cshockey@fundraisingu.net'),
	(272,103,'memberprofile','<p>I\'m Colin Shockey; I\'ve worked in the fundraising business now for five years. I was presented the opportunity to work with Mike Bahun in the spring of 2006 and I immediately jumped on the opportunity because if there is something I feel I can relate to, its with athletes and coaches.</p>\r\n<p>My father, Curt Shockey, has been a baseball coach in Nebraska for 29 years and I was fortunate enough to play high school baseball for him at Ralston High. I also played a little basketball for the Rams. A couple of high school achievements were, Athlete of the Year, two-time First Team All-State selection and three-time All-Conference selection.</p>\r\n<p>I then had the opportunity to play baseball in college. I attended Iowa Western CC, Nebraska (UNL) and Creighton, all on baseball scholarships. At Iowa Western I was an Academic All-American and in 2005 I helped the Jays win the Missouri Valley Regular Season Championship.</p>\r\n<p>I finally finished up school at University of Nebraska at Omaha, where I got a degree in criminal justice and minored in psychology. Which leads us back to, how does a person with a criminal justice background get involved in business? Well, like I said, I saw a great opportunity to work with coaches and athletes and felt this was the perfect fit for me. And it\'s been great.</p>\r\n<p>I\'ve been married to my wife, Jessica, for four years.  We have great young boys, Easton and Kyler.</p>'),
