	(291,105,'member_email',''),
	(292,105,'memberprofile','<p>I\'m a 1999 graduate from Omaha Burke H.S. where I was a 3-year letter winner in baseball. Right after high school, I attended Baylor University where I was a member of the 2000 Big XII Championship baseball team. In 2001, I transferred back home to play for Iowa Western Community College and I was a member of the 2001 Junior College World Series qualifying team. After graduating from IWCC in 2002, I finished up my playing career for the University of Missouri - Columbia in 2003 &amp; 2004. While at Mizzou, I was a member of Big XII Tournament &amp; NCAA Regional Qualifying teams both seasons. I graduated in 2004 with a major in General Studies focusing in business, sociology and communications.</p>\r\n<p>After graduation I moved back to Omaha and met my wife, Sara, who attended Millard West H.S. and ran cross country for Creighton University. She eventually graduated from the University of Nebraska Medical Center as a Doctor of Pharmacy, and she now works as a pharmacist in Omaha. We have two beautiful children; Kendall Jo was born in February 2008 and Brett Allen was born in January 2010.</p>'),
