	(321,108,'memberprofile','<p>I am from Topeka, KS where I attended Topeka West High School. At Topeka West I participated in football, wrestling, track &amp; field, marching band &amp; symphonic band. After graduating in 2002 from Topeka West I went to Benedictine College in Atchison, KS where I played football lettering for four years, all-conference for three, and all-american honorable mention my senior season. In this time I was team captain for the Benedictine Ravens and the 2005 NAIA Champions of Character award recipient as nominated by coaches and peers. At Benedictine College I earned my degree in Philosophy and Theology. While completing my degree I coached college football for one season, then high school wrestling for one season. Upon graduating I began working in the Benedictine College Admission Office. In my three &amp; a half years at Benedictine I functioned as the Assistant &amp; Associate Director of Admission. My wife Jenna and I live in Kansas City, Missouri where she is an occupational therapist. We have been married one year. I am extremely excited about my opportunity to serve the coaches, athletes, directors and musicians in this position as a fundraising consultant with Fundraising University. Currently, I am a volunteer assistant on the Oak Park wrestling staff in Missouri.</p>'),
