	(331,109,'memberprofile','<p>My name is Chris Miller. I\'ve been working in the High School fundraising business for over 2 years. I\'ve had some great experiences both in North Carolina and in Colorado and am very excited to be back in Colorado and a part of the Fundraising University team. Colorado is a beautiful place and there is no place I\'d rather be!</p>\r\n<p>My passion is High School athletics. I played soccer, baseball and basketball in High School. My experience as an athlete has molded me into the person I am today. Helping programs achieve their financial goals and be more competitive is very rewarding and is why I love my career so much. </p>\r\n<p>I received my Bachelors in Business in 2005 from Miami University. Since earning my degree, I always knew that I wanted and needed to be involved in athletics. Resources for High School sports programs are minimal at best. Fundraising can be difficult and time consuming. What we offer our coaches is a simple, easy, and defined approach to fundraising. Our core principles are no different than a coach\'s. Let\'s put together a game plan, diligently prepare and finally execute. With years of experience, we can manage your fundraiser and take out the guess work. </p>\r\n<p>I look forward to taking part in your programs growth for years to come.</p>'),
